overview: "The user's intent was to centralize and structure all project
  documentation for a sleep questionnaire application, making it easier to track
  and validate against the developed app. The agent began by exploring existing
  documents, identifying unreadable binary files. Following the user's
  instruction, the agent converted these .docx and .pdf files into readable text
  formats using command-line tools. The core approach involved creating a
  dedicated  directory to archive original source materials and
  then synthesizing the information into two comprehensive Markdown files:
   for high-level project scope, functional needs, and a
  validation checklist, and  for granular details on
  questions, scoring logic, and diagnostic criteria. This resulted in a
  well-organized and accessible set of documentation for the sleep questionnaire
  application."
